sheMelt.name: sheMelt

revisions.description: Update after review. Define more detailed measurment result types.
Modify unit of foreignCurrent result parameters from mA to uA.

sheMelt.contactinfo: Gerd Barchmann COO BCS DSLAM RD SDE HW1 gerd.barchmann@nsn.com
sheMelt.description: Definition of MELT (metallic line testing) feature control commands and results. New supported with R3.7M.

SheMeltTestRequestIfStateType.name: SheMeltTestRequestIfStateType
SheMeltTestRequestIfStateType.description: The MELT state of a port (IfIndex). idle -> no test running and test was never started since IU reset beingTested -> test is running applyingTestTone -> test tone activated on line testSucceeded(5) -> line idle and MELT was successful finished testAborted -> line idle and MELT aborted by operator or internal failure/timeout

SheMeltTestRequestIuStateType.name: SheMeltTestRequestIuStateType
SheMeltTestRequestIuStateType.description: The MELT state type of concerned IU. idle -> no port of this iu under test - new test could be started beingTested -> one port of this iu is currently under test - no new test could be started applyingTestTone -> one port of this iu has currently a test tone activated - no new test could be started

SheMeltControlReqType.name: SheMeltControlReqType
SheMeltControlReqType.description: The type for MELT test commands.

SheMeltControlReqResultType.name: SheMeltControlReqResultType
SheMeltControlReqResultType.description: The result type for MELT command.

SheMeltTestResultStateType.name: SheMeltTestResultStateType
SheMeltTestResultStateType.description: Status of the information contained in MeltTestResultTable. Values: notTested -> port was not tested since reset, all results not valid testFailed -> port was tested but test failed, all results not valid testSucceeded -> port was tested successfuly, check single result valid information

SheMeltTestResultValidType.name: SheMeltTestResultValidType
SheMeltTestResultValidType.description: Valid information for each single MELT result value. Values: invalid -> the shown result is not valid (maybe the test could not run because of external conditions) valid -> trusted result aboveLimitOfMeasurementRange -> result is above HW measurement range belowLimitOfMeasurementRange -> result is below HW measurement range

sheMeltTestRequestStateTable.name: sheMeltTestRequestStateTable
sheMeltTestRequestStateTable.description: Each entry in this table contains the testing status of each IfIndex. Only indeces of MELT feature supporting interfaces are listed in this table!

sheMeltTestRequestIfState.name: sheMeltTestRequestIfState
sheMeltTestRequestIfState.description: The MELT status of this interface. Only one port of one IU could be under test at time. Ports on different IU's could be under test at the same time. Check the corresponding sheMeltTestRequestIuState for this precondition. NOTE: Wetting current injection will be autonomously interrupted, if MELT or testTone insertion is started (WC configuration himself via sheXdslMib or sheShdslMib) for this interface as long as the test is running. Forgetting to stop test tone insertion will inhibit wetting current!

sheMeltTestRequestIuState.name: sheMeltTestRequestIuState
sheMeltTestRequestIuState.description: The MELT status of IU where this interface is located on. Every port must know whether this IU is under melt test already or not, in order to decide if the melt test request on this port can be accepted. Only one port of one IU could be under test at time. Ports on different IU's could be under test at the same time.

sheMeltTestRequestTestToneIndex.name: sheMeltTestRequestTestToneIndex
sheMeltTestRequestTestToneIndex.description: This parameter points on a valid entry of sheMeltTestToneTable. These configuration is needed for test tone insertion on this line. One default profile with index 1 will always exist and is assigned per default to each line!

sheMeltTestRequestControlReq.name: sheMeltTestRequestControlReq
sheMeltTestRequestControlReq.description: setMeltTestParameters (1): sheMeltTestRequestControlParameterFreq1 startMeltTest (2): sheMeltTestRequestControlIndex stopMeltTest (3): sheMeltTestRequestControlIndex activateTestTone (4): sheMeltTestRequestControlIndex deactivateTestTone (5): sheMeltTestRequestControlIndex setMeltTestRequestTestToneIndex (8): sheMeltTestRequestControlIndex sheMeltTestRequestControlTestToneIndex

sheMeltTestRequestControlIndex.name: sheMeltTestRequestControlIndex
sheMeltTestRequestControlIndex.description: The interface index of the DSL central PPTP which should be configured.

sheMeltTestRequestControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheMeltTestRequestControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheMeltTestRequestControlReqTimeStamp.name: sheMeltTestRequestControlReqTimeStamp
sheMeltTestRequestControlReqTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheMeltTestToneTable.name: sheMeltTestToneTable
sheMeltTestToneTable.description: Each entry in this table contains a set of parameters for test tone generation. These entries could be assigned to each interface. One default entry exist which could NOT be modified or deleted!

sheMeltTestToneIndex.name: sheMeltTestToneIndex
sheMeltTestToneIndex.description: This parameter is index of sheMeltTestToneTable. This configuration is needed for test tone insertion on the line. One default profile with index 1 will always exist and is assigned per default to each line!

sheMeltTestToneControlReq.description: createMeltTestToneEntry (10): (index will autonomously generated by NE) sheMeltTestToneControlFreq1 sheMeltTestToneControlFreq2 sheMeltTestToneControlLevel modifyMeltTestToneEntry (11): sheMeltTestToneControlIndex sheMeltTestToneControlFreq1 sheMeltTestToneControlFreq2 sheMeltTestToneControlLevel deleteMeltTestToneEntry (12): sheMeltTestToneControlIndex
